solution: Since the units digits of $7 \cdot 17 \cdot 1977$ and $7^3$ are the same, their difference has a units digit of $\boxed{0}$.

$7 \cdot 17 \cdot 1977 - 7^3 = 22119 - 343$

Now we can find the units digit of the result:

Units digit of $22119$: 9
Units digit of $343$: 3

Subtracting the units digits, we get $9 - 3 = 6$

Therefore, the units digit of $7 \cdot 17 \cdot 1977 - 7^3$ is $\boxed{6}$.
